101. Identify, how a cookie’s value can be retrieved in a web application?
Cookies are stored client-side but accessed on the server through $_COOKIE.
•	You retrieve it using $_COOKIE['cookieName'].
•	Always check with isset() before using.
<?php
setcookie("user", "Kavya", time()+3600, "/"); // set cookie
if (isset($_COOKIE["user"])) {
    echo "Cookie Value: " . $_COOKIE["user"];
} else {
    echo "Cookie not set yet!";
}
?>
